UPDATE: SunMoon Food parent Shanghai Yiguo files for bankruptcy; stock slumps 22%.Shanghai Yiguo E-Commerce is the ultimate holding company of Yiguo General Food Pte Ltd  which in turn holds a 59.9% stake in SunMoon as of Monday. SunMoon distributes fresh fruits  vegetables  seafood  and meat  focusing on the South-east Asian and Greater China markets.SunMoon noted that there is no certainty as to the collectability of the trade receivables which amounts to some $12.4 million in account receivables. The board of SunMoon has set up an executive committee to advise the company on the matter including the filing of the proof of debt.
